    <name>
      <text>6.1.16 (Find equation of tangent)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Find the equation of the tangent to the circle with equation \({@expand(circ3)@}=0\) at the point P({@px@}, {@py@}). Write your answer in the form <code>ax + by + c = 0</code></p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] = 0</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Begin by writing the given equation in centre-radius form. Completing the square with \(x\) and \(y\) gives
\[
{@expand(circ3)@} = 0 \implies {@circ2@}.
\]
Thus the centre of the circle is \(C({@-gg@}, {@-ff@})\). Now the gradient of the radius CP is given by 
\[
m_{rad} = \frac{{@py@} - {@-ff@}}{{@px@} - {@-gg@}} = {@mrad@}.
\]
Hence \(m_{tan} = \frac{-1}{m_{rad}}= {@mtan@}\).

Then using the equation \( y - b = m (x - a)\) with \(a = {@px@}, b = {@py@}, m = {@mtan@}\) and rearranging we get that the equation of the tangent is 
\[
{@ta1@}=0
\]</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
